<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1107,1413]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,320,1227,1253]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunetti, 1913" authorityName="Brunetti" authorityYear="1913" box="[697,1058,1227,1253]" class="Insecta" family="Tipulidae" genus="Brithura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imperfecta">
<emphasis box="[697,857,1227,1252]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">B. imperfecta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brunetti" box="[875,1050,1227,1253]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" refString="Brunetti, E. (1913) New and interesting Diptera from the eastern Himalayas. Records of the Indian Museum, 9, 255 - 277." type="journal article" year="1913">
Brunetti, 
<number box="[990,1050,1227,1253]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1913.0">1913</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having the dilated unbroken costa. It can be easily separated from the latter by having the strongly bent outer gonostylus and the dark brownish yellow wing. In 
<taxonomicName box="[460,618,1307,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Tipulidae" genus="Brithura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imperfecta">
<emphasis box="[460,618,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">B. imperfecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the outer gonostylus is slightly bent, with an erect slender rod on the outer margin (
<bibRefCitation author="Alexander" box="[316,510,1347,1373]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" refString="Alexander, C. P. (1970) New or little-known species of Asiatic Tipulidae (Diptera). III. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 96, 307 - 352." type="journal article" year="1970">
Alexander 
<number box="[447,510,1347,1373]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1970.0">1970</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,955,1387,1413]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="etymology">
